  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Needs and organisational assessment for supporting streetchildren</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burkina Faso is one of the poorest countries in the world. Many children in the second city of Bobo-Dioulasso end up on the streets. They face violence and miss out on school. Girls suffer worse sexual abuse and are drawn into prostitution. This project will research the needs of boys and girls on the street and who else is already helping them. It will also assess the strengths and weaknesses of the local agency and fund a financial audit. As a result, the partners will plan how to extend their street children work from the capital city to Bobo, especially to help girls experiencing sexual violence. They will ensure they have the skills and systems to bring effective long-term change.</narrative>
  </description>
